<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#800000">Originally posted by Parm Vomgrossenhirn on 10-11-2000 01:53 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Originally posted by Jabeker:
[b]Have many of you posting about these loathesome individuals actually seen them and been killed by them?

The first spawn aggros, but the later ones have a dubious or indifferent con.  Now I wasn't about to just go over and test it out, but if they do aggro, it's a really small range.  Most of the deaths I see are from people who misjudge the casters, or don't realize that the repop is stronger than the last one (attacking without conning first).

Whoever was whining about Rorer, that was supposedly fixed.

In Qeynos proper, there are now some wandering npcs that attack.  They seem pretty low level, but I don't really know how low.  I would complain about that before talking about anything in QH.  There is also a scoundrel wandering around, who is high level (but not aggro), but I wonder if he will help out the low level ones in a fight.[/b][/QUOTE]

My friend plays a lvl 35 human cleric.  He was on his way to Cazic two nights ago and got his butt handed to him by Rorer.  He was complaining about it over guildchat.

So no, he hasn't been changed yet.

I don't have firsthand experience of being killed by one of these guys, and I haven't run around looking all over the place to see who all is now there.  But as I was passing through Qeynos hills on my way to hop the boat to Erudin to pick up a lvl 44 enchanter spell, I noticed the new tent by the qeynos wall and as I approached a Rude Individual ran out from a fairly long distance (at least 50 feet) and started attacking me.  He was so deep green that I just casted Discordant Mind on him (6.1 second casting time) without interuption because he couldn't hit me.  He of course dropped like a sack of rocks to a single hit of 508 dmg.  I just looted his corpse (was empty) and then continued into Qeynos before something else spawned that I noticed.  So I don't know what happens next.

I did think it was odd that such a low green should run out and attack some PC who was obviously at least a couple dozen levels higher.  That is behavior one would normally expect to see from Zombies or skeletons or other undead.


------------------

Parm Vomgrossenhirn of Karana</TEXTAREA>
